# ---- Python ----
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.so
.Python
/build/
/dist/
develop-eggs/
downloads/
eggs/
.eggs/
# Anchored to the repo root: an unanchored "lib/" or "lib64/" also matches
# frontend/src/lib/, which silently dropped real committed source from a
# `git add frontend` (discovered when the JWST frontend's lib/ directory
# went missing from a commit). Python venvs are already excluded by name via
# .venv/, venv/, env/, ENV/ below, so these two are for a stray top-level
# build only.
/lib/
/lib64/
parts/
sdist/
var/
wheels/
*.egg-info/
.installed.cfg
*.egg
MANIFEST

# ---- Virtual environments ----
.venv/
venv/
env/
ENV/
.python-version

# ---- Testing, linting, typing caches ----
.pytest_cache/
.hypothesis/
.mypy_cache/
.pyright/
.ruff_cache/
.coverage
.coverage.*
htmlcov/
.tox/
.nox/

# ---- Jupyter ----
.ipynb_checkpoints/
*.ipynb_checkpoints

# ---- Editors and OS ----
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*~
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# ---- Logs ----
*.log

# ---- Secrets and local config ----
.env
.env.*
*.local
.claude/settings.local.json

# ============================================================
# Research data artefacts. Raw spectra and large archive
# products are NEVER committed. Only derived, lightweight
# catalogues and code live in this repository.
# See docs/04-data-sources.md and .claude/rules/data.md
# ============================================================

# Raw and downloaded archive products (MAST, NASA Exoplanet Archive).
# The lightweight inventory CSVs and fetch scripts under data/MAST/ and
# data/NASA_Archive/ ARE committed; only the bulk downloaded data products are
# ignored. The local filesystem is case-insensitive, so the patterns below must
# not collide with the committed data/MAST/ directory (an earlier "data/mast/"
# rule did, and was removed).
data/raw/
data/downloads/
data/cache/

# astroquery writes downloaded MAST products under a mastDownload/ tree
mastDownload/
data/MAST/mastDownload/

# Per-source working folders: downloaded raw spectra and generated plots. The
# folder and its README stay tracked so the layout is visible on a fresh clone;
# everything downloaded or generated inside is never committed. To keep a single
# curated figure, force-add it (for example: git add -f data/MAST/plots/x.png).
data/MAST/raw/*
!data/MAST/raw/README.md
data/MAST/plots/*
!data/MAST/plots/README.md
data/NASA_Archive/raw/*
!data/NASA_Archive/raw/README.md
data/NASA_Archive/plots/*
!data/NASA_Archive/plots/README.md

# Regenerable build output: the tidy per-point spectra table assembled from the
# downloaded .tbl files by build_nasa_spectra_dataset.py. Rebuild it locally; to
# track a curated copy, force-add it (git add -f).
data/NASA_Archive/nasa_miri_spectra_points.csv

# Regenerable build output: the numeric median spectra assembled from the
# git-ignored raw X1DINTS FITS by plot_mast_spectrum.py. Rebuild it locally.
data/MAST/mast_median_spectra.csv

# Bulk spectra in common astronomy and array formats
*.fits
*.fits.gz
*.h5
*.hdf5
*.npy
*.npz
# NASA Exoplanet Archive spectrum data files (IPAC table format)
*.tbl

# Generated synthetic training sets and model checkpoints
data/synthetic/
data/training/
models/
checkpoints/
*.pt
*.pth
*.ckpt
*.pkl
*.joblib

# Opacity tables and cross-section databases (large, fetched separately)
data/opacities/
opacity_data/

# Inference outputs and figures (regenerable)
outputs/
results/runs/
figures/

# Large derived catalogues (keep only the curated, small ones under version control by
# explicitly force-adding them, for example: git add -f data/catalogues/dataset_catalogue.csv)
data/catalogues/*.csv
